ZH: 我希望你了解我的立场。
EN: I hope you understand my position.

ZH: 请你了解学校的规则。
EN: Please understand the school rules.

ZH: 他不会了解你的感受。
EN: He won't understand your feelings.

ZH: 我们需要更多时间来了解这个问题。
EN: We need more time to understand this issue.

ZH: 你能了解我说的话吗？
EN: Can you understand what I'm saying?

ZH: 他不了解这个城市的文化。
EN: He doesn't understand the culture of this city.

ZH: 她很难了解他的决定。
EN: She finds it difficult to understand his decision.

ZH: 让我们一起努力了解这个难题。
EN: Let's work together to understand this difficult problem.

ZH: 你必须要了解你的责任。
EN: You must understand your responsibilities.

ZH: 老师很耐心地教我们要如何了解这个理论。
EN: The teacher patiently teaches us how to understand this theory.

ZH: 他花了很多时间了解这个领域。
EN: He spent a lot of time understanding this field.

ZH: 我们需要更多信息才能了解真相。
EN: We need more information to understand the truth.

ZH: 在跟进的过程中，需要了解客户的需求。
EN: In the follow-up process, it is necessary to understand the needs of the customers.

ZH: 我们需要更多时间来了解彼此。
EN: We need more time to understand each other.

ZH: 老板希望你能明白她的决定。
EN: The boss hopes you can understand her decision.

ZH: 学生需要深入了解这个概念。
EN: Students need to deeply understand this concept.

ZH: 你应该了解这是一个很重要的问题。
EN: You should understand that this is a very important issue.

ZH: 请你耐心地了解我的困难。
EN: Please be patient in understanding my difficulties.

ZH: 我们需要了解客户的需求才能提供更好的服务。
EN: We need to understand the customer's needs in order to provide better service.

ZH: 请你努力了解他的立场。
EN: Please make an effort to understand his position.
